subSubSection.paragraph:
Genitalia
(
Figs 34
A–B, 47): tegumen more or less quadrate, with proximal margin sinuous and distal margin convex (
Fig. 34C
), in lateral view, shorter than length of gnathos; ventral arm of tegumen longer than dorsal arm of saccus (
Fig. 34A
). Saccus longer than tegumen+uncus, base shorter than lateral margin (
Fig. 34B
). Uncus, in dorsal view, rectangular, twice longer than wide, as long as tegumen and without disto-lateral projections, distal margin rounded (
Fig. 34C
). Gnathos as in the other species of the group (
Fig. 34A, D
). Valva three times longer than wide; sacculus more than 1/2 width of valva; costa rectangular not contiguous with ampulla; ampulla narrow and as long as costa; ventral process of harpe narrow, cylindrical, longer than tegumen+uncus and slightly arched inwards in dorsal view, with apical setae thick and long and ventral margin convex; dorsal process on median portion, rounded in dorsal view and wider than ventral process (
Fig. 34
E–F). Aedeagus as long as valva, strongly curved dorsally; ventral projection distally wide and slightly curved ventrally (
Fig. 34
G–J); posterior end of cornutus rectangular, with thick distal spines, curved laterally (
Fig. 47
).
